						<summary>

						<p>Stone near the <hi rend="italic">dhvaja-staṁbha</hi> in the Chennakēśava śvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1520 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the Śaka 1442, Vikrama, • • • • • bu. 3, Thursday, Makarasaṅkramaṇa corresponding to 27th December, 1520 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged, mentions the son (name not clear) of a certain <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Rāchirāja Basavayyadēva and registers some gifts made by him.</p>						

						</summary>
